Text.Value: Don't I wish. The gnome's a True Soul.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player holds out hands to the duergar. They look them over.

Text.Value: Look at the top-dwarf getting all judgy. Not like you lot came to our rescue when mind flayers yoked us.
True Soul, yeah? Tell your chums we won't move a pebble.
Fine, take a look.
Now jump to it, or it's up the lift and straight to the shadows.
Cruelty like that poisons the soul 'til one day, you drop dead - or the person you're fucking with snaps and puts a sword in your eye.
A waste of a slave. He should be digging or scavenging, not... serving drinks.
You flirt.
Five workin' fingers. A bit stubby. Prime for digging.

RuleGroup.RuleString: DROWHALFELF or ELF or GITHYANKI or HALFELF

Text.Value: Five workin' fingers. Nice and bony, prime for digging.
Five workin' fingers. Nice and meaty, prime for digging.
You want to see my hands? What for?
Moan all you want - we're born with parts to play. I was born a master, and Stickshit was born a slave.
Damned slavers. Just the sight of them turns my stomach.
Coming right up, Pisspot.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
To Magmar

Stickpit returns with two beer mugs

Text.Value: Scowl all you want. You got five workin' fingers, perfect for digging.
Heard you caused a ruckus. But I'm keeping my butt planted.
You just take one. They're swarming the place!
That's just the way of it.
Pisspot.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
To Magmar

Stickpit walks off screen with both mugs

Text.Value: You heard the man. Let's see 'em.
Leave.

EditorData.stateContext: Magmar and Pistole holding drinks for this scene.

Text.Value: Enslaving the meek? I see you live up to your cruel reputation.
Look at ya. Like a slab of cold iron come to life. Made for hard labour.
Hold out your hands, clan-sen.
Hold out your hands, hoon.
Hey Stickshit? Where's my drink?
If I was that slave, I'd be tempted to add a dash of something poisonous to their drinks.
You want respect? Let your Absolute pay for it. 'Til then, bugger off.
True Soul, yeah? Tell the sergeant we won't move a pebble.
I think we've found two duergar who are going to get spit in their drinks.
I don't like your attitude.
You want bygones staying bygones? You keep to your business, and we'll keep to ours.
Prick-squeak - tell the sergeant we won't move a pebble 'til we're paid.
Then you'll appreciate how few shits I have to give ya.
Besides, nothin' mundane about serving good brew. Stuff's the balm of life, and Stickshit there's got the honour.
Heard you tore Nere t'bits. But that don't make us friends.
I heard a True Soul was trapped. Shouldn't you be helping?
You disgust me, slaver. How do you live with yourself?
Now that's how you motivate the staff.
Laduguer's guts - it's time I shut you up.
Some thoughts aren't meant to be said aloud. That was one of them.
You're quite the blowhard. I can appreciate that.
I kick up my feet, order a brew, watch 'em work. They'll complain, but they love it, I'm telling you.
And I don't like pigshit, but damned if your mouth ain't spewing it.
Comfortably. Figured it obvious.
Another round, Stickshit.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
To Skickpit

Stickpit is collecting empty tankards from Magmar and Pistle

Text.Value: Your captive is most entertaining. How might I get one of my own?
Less asking. More showing.
Here's to Smug. Nasty prick.

To Pistle

Magmar and Pistle both holding beermugs

Text.Value: A True Soul is trapped in a cave-in. Shouldn't you be digging him out?
You can't swing a greataxe without hittin' a pocket-runt. Stickshit won't be missed.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The two duergar take a drink and set their mugs down.

Text.Value: Attack.
Next time your mind sinks that low, keep things to yourself.
Frown and keep your hands to yourself.
Magmar. We got another one.

Text.Value: Stickshit talks like Smug when he wrecked that 'shroom village...

EditorData.NodeContext: Starting to laugh as you tell a 'joke', drunk and laughing

Text.Value: They'll squirm a bit, maybe give you some lip.
... and then shagged it!

EditorData.NodeContext: pissing laughing at Magmar. The joke doesn't even make sense but it's hilarious to pistle

Text.Value: Prick-squeak - go tell your True Soul chums we won't move a pebble.
Your slave was made to toil. You're squandering him on mundane tasks.
'Course at your size, might be tough pinning 'em down. Would pay to see it, not gonna lie.
All it takes is a stiff crop to get 'em in line.
Well shit.
You want Nere, you claw him out. My drinking hand's busy.
How dare you enslave my people? They deserve dignity, not servitude.

Synopsis: Two surly duergar with foul mouths order a gnome slave around. Both should sound DRUNK, loud and obnoxious as they demand a refil from the gnome. Player can assert how they feel about the enslaving of the gnome.
